HEADWORD: Blowzed
<hw>Blowzed</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having high color
from exposure to the weather; ruddy-faced; blowzy; disordered.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Huge women <qex>blowzed</qex> with health and wind.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Blowzy</ent>⟦br⟧
